Package com.telenav.kivakit.resource

Interface ResourceFolder<T extends ResourceFolder<T>>

All Superinterfaces:
com.telenav.kivakit.core.messaging.Broadcaster, com.telenav.kivakit.core.messaging.Listener, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.comparison.Matchable<ResourcePathed>, com.telenav.kivakit.core.messaging.MessageTransceiver, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.Nameable, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.NamedObject, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.messaging.Receiver, com.telenav.kivakit.core.messaging.Repeater, ResourcePathed, com.telenav.kivakit.core.messaging.Transceiver, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.messaging.Transmitter, UriIdentified
All Known Implementing Classes:
Folder, Package
public interface ResourceFolder<T extends ResourceFolder<T>> extends com.telenav.kivakit.core.messaging.Repeater, UriIdentified, ResourcePathed, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.comparison.Matchable<ResourcePathed>
A resource container is an abstraction that provides access to hierarchical resources, independent of implementation. Folder is a ResourceFolder, but Package is also a resource folder.

Contents

  • resources() - The resources in this folder
  • resources(Matcher) - The matching files in this folder
  • folders() - The folders in this folder
  • resources(Matcher) - The matching folders in this folder
  • nestedResources(Matcher) ()} - All nested files in this folder
  • nestedResources(Matcher) - All matching nested files in this folder
  • nestedFolders(Matcher) - All matching nested folders under this folder
  • temporaryFile(FileName) - A temporary file in this folder with the given name
  • temporaryFile(FileName, Extension) - A temporary file in this folder with the given name and extension
  • temporaryFolder(FileName) - A temporary sub-folder with the given name

Hierarchy

  • absolute() - This folder with an absolute path
  • ResourcePathed.path() - The path to this folder
  • parent() - The parent folder, or null if there is none
  • relativeTo(ResourceFolder) - This folder with a path relative to the given folder
  • resource(FileName) - The file with the given name in this folder
  • folder(String) - The folder with the given name in this folder

Operations

  • copyTo(Folder, WriteMode, ProgressReporter)
  • copyTo(Folder, WriteMode, Matcher, ProgressReporter)
  • copyTo(Folder, WriteMode, FolderCopyMode, Matcher, ProgressReporter)
  • delete() - Deletes this folder if it is empty
  • mkdirs() - Creates this folder and any required parent folders
  • renameTo(ResourceFolder) - Renames this folder to the given folder

Checks

  • exists() - True if this folder exists
  • isEmpty() - True if this folder is empty
  • isMaterialized() - True if this folder exists locally
  • isWritable() - True if this folder can be written to

Conversions

  • ResourcePathed.asJavaFile() - This folder as a File
  • absolute() - This folder with an absolute path
